Manila first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Manila had a population of 798. The population density was {{convert|1,144.9|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Manila was 621 (77.8%) [[White Americans|White]], 11 (1.4%) [[African Americans|African American]], 27 (3.4%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 8 (1.0%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 3 (0.4%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 32 (4.0%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 96 (12.0%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 83 persons (10.4%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Manila CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0645414 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 28, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 361 households, out of which 67 (18.6%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 106 (29.4%) were married-couple households, 59 (16.3%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 67 (18.6%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 129 (35.7%) had a male householder with no partner present. 121 households (33.5%) were one person, and 49 (13.6%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.21.<ref name=DP1/> There were 178 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (49.3% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Manila CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0645414 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 28, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 123 people (15.4%) under the age of 18, 77 people (9.6%) aged 18 to 24, 266 people (33.3%) aged 25 to 44, 184 people (23.1%) aged 45 to 64, and 148 people (18.5%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 39.4{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 112.8 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 400 housing units at an average density of {{convert|573.9|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 361 (90.3%) were occupied. Of these, 174 (48.2%) were owner-occupied, and 187 (51.8%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

